---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Engineering Journal: July 2026">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono">
        <span>Journal</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>July 2026</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        Engineering Journal: July 2026
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        A monthly log of things built, concepts learned, books read, system failures, and next milestones.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Content Sections -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-10 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      
      <!-- Built -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Built</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          I restructured this entire portfolio site into a clean, typography-focused publication platform using Astro.
          I also implemented partial indexes and exclusion constraints for the DailyDine Go scheduling engine database schema.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Learned -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Learned</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          I spent time learning the details of Postgres Multi-Version Concurrency Control (MVCC) and transaction isolation levels.
          I also studied token signature verification boundaries, memory overflow stacking in compiled C binaries, and the TCP sliding window protocol mechanics.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Read -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Read</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          I started reading Martin Kleppmann's <strong class="text-[#FAFAFA] font-medium">Designing Data-Intensive Applications</strong> (completed 18%).
          I also read Ken Thompson's classic paper, <strong class="text-[#FAFAFA] font-medium">Reflections on Trusting Trust</strong>, which discusses compiler security.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Failed -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Failed</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          I spent three days trying to configure a complex Redis distributed lock mechanism for table bookings.
          It introduced race conditions during network blips and made recovery logic complicated.
          I deleted the Redis code entirely and replaced it with native database transaction isolates.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Next Month -->
      <section class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <h2 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-semibold">Next Month</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA]">
          My priority for August is to implement index migrations to IndexedDB for HisabProx,
          and study advanced Linux network packet filtering using iptables rulesets.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- Article Footer -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-8 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pt-12 mt-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <h4 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-medium font-mono font-semibold">Other Journals</h4>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <span class="text-[#71717A]">August 2026 (Coming Soon)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
